    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/1300</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of Staff of the United States Army (<persName
                            corresp="#p_MGD1" type="from">MacArthur</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-25">July 25,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: At the request of the Secretary
                    of War,<note n="25" xml:id="d391fn25">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Patrick J. Hurley</persName>.</note> receipt is
                    acknowledged of your letter of July 8th,<note n="26" xml:id="d391fn26">Not
                        printed.</note> wherein you request the cooperation of the War Department in
                    accomplishing an aerial photographic project of an area on the
                    Guatemala-Honduras boundary for the Guatemala-Honduras Special Boundary
                    Tribunal.</p>
                <p>The project indicated can be accomplished by the Army Air Corps, provided the Air
                    Corps is reimbursed for the cost of making the photographs, such cost to be
                    confined to the actual cost of gasoline, oil, film, paper, chemicals, the labor
                    performed in developing the photographic negatives and the printing of copies of
                    photographs, and the per diem expenses of the personnel as authorized by law,
                    together with such incidental expenses as care and minor repairs to airplane and
                    transportation of personnel to and from project.</p>
                <p>It is desired that the Department of State secure the necessary authorization for
                    Army personnel and airplane with aerial photographic equipment, to pass through
                    Panama, Costa Rica, Nicaragua, Salvador, Honduras and Guatemala.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas MacArthur</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
